Paul-Louis Roubert (born 1967) is an associate researcher at the Laboratoire d'histoire visuelle contemporaine, senior lecturer in photography at Paris 8 University and, since December 2010, president of the Soci&lt;U+00E9&gt;t&lt;U+00E9&gt; fran&lt;U+00E7&gt;aise de photographie.12
Roubert was awarded a doctorate in 2004 on the basis of his thesis on L'Introduction du mod&lt;U+00E8&gt;le photographique dans la critique d'art en France which led to L'Image sans qualit&lt;U+00E9&gt;s published in 2006. He has been closely connected to the Soci&lt;U+00E9&gt;t&lt;U+00E9&gt; fran&lt;U+00E7&gt;aise de photographie whose bulletin he edited from 1999 to 2004. Since 1996, He has been a founding member of the journal Etudes photographiques. He has lectured in the history of photography at Paris 8, Paris 1 and at the &lt;U+00C9&gt;cole des hautes &lt;U+00E9&gt;tudes en sciences sociales. In December 2010, he was unanimously elected president of the Soci&lt;U+00E9&gt;t&lt;U+00E9&gt; fran&lt;U+00E7&gt;aise de photographie.34
Main publications

&quot;L'Image sans qualit&lt;U+00E9&gt;s&quot;. Les beaux-arts et la critique &lt;U+00E0&gt; l'&lt;U+00E9&gt;preuve de la photographie, 1839-1859, Paris, Monum, 2006.
&quot;Le daguerr&lt;U+00E9&gt;otype en proc&lt;U+00E8&gt;s&quot;, Le Daguerr&lt;U+00E9&gt;otype fran&lt;U+00E7&gt;ais. Un objet photographique (cat. exp.), Paris, Mus&lt;U+00E9&gt;e d&lt;U+2019&gt;Orsay/RMN, 2003, p. 119-131.
&quot;1859. Exposer la photographie&quot;, &lt;U+00C9&gt;tudes photographiques.

